Mesoscutum with engraved and strong reticulation, posterior 1 / 3 with or without a weak median groove (
Fig. 29
); notaular depressions smooth and shiny. Scutellum slightly convex to flat with engraved and strong reticulation, laterally and posteriorly smooth (
Fig. 29
). Axillae with engraved and very weak reticulation (
Fig. 29
). Dorsellum smooth with two large foveae anterolaterally (
Fig. 30
). Propodeal callus with two setae (
Fig. 30
). Forewing rounded, speculum closed below. Petiolar foramen triangular.

Petiole dorsally smooth and shiny, 0.5–0.7 X as long as wide, mediolaterally with a spine (
Fig. 30
). Gaster elongate with apex pointed.
